[thinking] **Considering Mockito in native testing**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about the need for metadata in Mockito subclass mock generation when working in native environments. I believe the tests are already set to mock correctly, so this should run smoothly. On native GraalImageCode, it seems WithIsolatedLoader can handle the subclass mock by creating a wrapper if the metadata is there. I wonder if error catching is necessary; perhaps ordinary dynamic bytecode mock generation isn’t possible in native. I'll consider using AssertJ for my assertions and finally write it all out!
